children":[{"type":"text","value":"But there’s another way. A way to have a website that never goes down. A website that quietly maintains itself, is safe and secure, and remains unchanged as it goes from 100 visitors a month to 100 visitors a minute.","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1,"offset":322},"end":{"line":10,"column":217,"offset":538},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1,"offset":322},"end":{"line":10,"column":217,"offset":538},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"The idea of a single server serving traffic for a website harks back toan age of mainframes and ISDN lines. But the demands of scale and perfect uptime killed the mainframe. Maybe it’s time they killed single-server sites as well.","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":540},"end":{"line":12,"column":231,"offset":770},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":540},"end":{"line":12,"column":231,"offset":770},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"A server is a complicated piece of equipment. It needs to be updated. Any of the two hundred processes running on it has the power to cripple the machine. It will stubbornly refuse to serve more requests than it can handle. It will shutdown in the middle of the night, or the middle of your vacation.","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":772},"end":{"line":14,"column":301,"offset":1072},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":772},"end":{"line":14,"column":301,"offset":1072},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Your homepage and marketing pages shouldn’t need to connect to a database. If your marketing site is opening a database connection just to render, you have a very finite limit on how many requests you can serve.","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":1074},"end":{"line":16,"column":212,"offset":1285},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line